<div class="story-body">
  <p>Singapore ranked first in 2016, followed by the United States, and then Malaysia. 
    With the 2018 index, the United Kingdom, United States, and France made up the top 3. 
    Singapore was ranked sixth, and Malaysia ranked eighth. 
    That doesn't mean, however, that Singapore and Malaysia "fell" on its cybersecurity efforts, or that it declined in its abilities and controls, since both increased their index score. 
    The global rankings are more to show who is further along in their programs, but doesn't say one is "better" or "worse" in their efforts.  </p>
  <p>Cybersecurity is a process, not a journey. 
    There is no "end" because there is always room for refinement, and the countries are well on their way.</p>
